comment: [Detectable with stop watch] Jordan (LAC) is in the lane without actively guarding for about 4 secs when he is imminently clearing. Holiday's (OKC) drive complicates the play since, had he drove straight and Jordan picked him up, Jordan would have been iminently legal at the start of his drive.
Redick (LAC) makes contact to the arm of Evans (NOP) and affects his shot attempt.
Evans (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Crawford (LAC).
Davis (NOP) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Holiday (NOP) makes contact with Jordan's (LAC) arm.
Anderson (NOP) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Cole (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Crawford's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Crawford (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Holiday (NOP).
Jordan (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Davis' (NOP) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Holiday (NOP) commits a take foul on Paul (LAC).
Rivers (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Holiday (NOP) and does not affect his RSBQ.
Gordon (NOP) commits a take foul on Paul (LAC).
